	 <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>86 threads, <a href=/strategy/races.html?race=6&start=0>1</a> <a href=/strategy/races.html?race=6&start=25>2</a> <a href=/strategy/races.html?race=6&start=50>3</a> <a href=/strategy/races.html?race=6&start=75>4</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=/strategy/races.html?race=6&start=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><ul><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99794357572289></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99794357572289><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/races.html?race=6&mid=99794357572289>How to pay for spells</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=86112><span id= >Mahotoko</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 16th 2:32 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you're an Erudite caster that follows Quellious and you're still hanging around the home island, I stumbled across something you might find useful.<br><br>I'm a seventh season mage who hasn't gone much beyond Qeynos, and the best moneymaker I've found so far is the temple of Quellious in Erudin which has a quest for bone chips. For six chips they give 3-4 gold (on average), an item (cleric spells, containers, weapons and armor), XP and faction. That's a lot more than you'll get for rat whiskers or bat wings. The trick for me has been finding the decaying skeletons to get the chips from, but I think I've solved that.<br><br>I went to check out The Warrens tonight just to see if I could make it, then bring along my group later. I did get killed once by the guards just inside Paineeel (the ones outside were indifferent, to my surprise) but I was able to make it and see that I would definitely need help with all those kobolds. On my way out, I took a look around the Paineel Newbie Garden and... it was beautiful. Decaying skeletons everywhere, and I had the whole place to myself. I made sure to steer clear of the guards by the exit, and then killed decaying skeletons until I was completely loaded down with bone chips and weapons. Only once did I encounter anything remotely dangerous, and that was a lost pet that was blue for me. Once I was done, I gated back to Erudin and visited Quellious' temple. For two hours' work I got enough to buy three level 8 spells. Time well spent, in my opinion.<br><br>I don't know if non-Erudites can receive this quest (you have to get a box from the guy) but if he'll go along with it I urge you to kill any skeleton you see and save the bone chips. And if you really want to make money, go harvest Paineel's newbie garden.<br><br>If only I knew a way to get XP as easily.<br><br>Mahokoto<br>7th Season Mage<br>Solusek Ro Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
