</ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99787687156908></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99787687156908><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/races.html?race=6&mid=99787687156908>Qeynos for Erudite newbies? NEVER!</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 15th 8:01 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've had a couple of Erudites start off in these parts, and I disagree with those who want to head to Qeynos to spend their newbie seasons.  Sure, it's easier to go beat on sankes, rats and bats by the light of day with 40 other people, but it takes a special person to walk out into the darkness of Toxxulia and take on the Kobald hordes by yourself.<br><br>Don't get me wrong.  Qeynos is a quaint, charming town with many lovely shops, and the first thing I do after receiving my guild robe and master's encouraging words is catch the boat for Antonica.  However, this is only to deliver some mail so I can purchase another spell or two, and pick up one of those nice 10-slot tax collection boxes from Vicus Nonad (good for storing various small items from your travels).  Deposit everything in bank, then commit suicide for a quick trip back to Odus -- I find those boat rides so tiring...<br><br>Toxx is a great place to hunt because it builds character ("puts hair on your chest" as the more masculine might say).  You HAVE to learn your skills to survive here -- none of this beating on moss snakes while a dozen other puny animals amble by harmlessly. Kobolds drop better loot too.  Backpacks and other items for storage are great.  The 'useless' caps dropped by the scouts can be turned in to the abandoned heretic pets near necro hut for gems -- if you are lucky, you might get an emerald which is worth 10-12pp to the vendors.  Some of the even carry booze, which is nice to drink after a long day of hunting.<br><br>Scared to wander off into the dark?  Use your magic to pull the beasties onto the porch, as the guards are not prone to KSing like the wandering Qeynos guards.  Killing Kobolds also helps build faction with Heretics, just in case you really want to prove your bravery later on by going into Paineel and the Warrens.<br><br>So go to Qeynos if you must.  Just leaves more for me...<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99792756363888></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99792756363888><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/races.html?race=6&mid=99792756363888>RE: Qeynos for Erudite newbies? NEVER!</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 15th 10:06 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Forgot one other important benefit: being the only Erudite on that side of Toxx means that you get to run shopping errands for dark elves and other evil types who can't go into Erudin -- can net quite a bit of money for that (made 20pp the other day buying two spells in a couple of minutes).<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
