<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99598020821925></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99598020821925><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/races.html?race=6&mid=99598020821925>RE: Starting points for Erud. Wiz.</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=1200><span id=Scholar>Thayn</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>51 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 24th 9:10 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.32]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My 2cp worth is to max int and then go str. The whys of this are simple. At low levels, you are talking a VERY small boost, maybe 1 hit in the whole fight. I understand that this can make the difference at low levels, but you will find yourself taking as much time to level through 20s and 30s as you did getting thru levels 1 thru 8 combined.<br><br>However, at higher levels, you will want to be able to kill more and stay out from vendors longer to make the exp. This is where greater STR takes a hand. The capacity to carry more without hurting your movement rate (Hence your kiting ability) is invaluable. However, a 5 pt HP boost won't matter much when a mob is hitting for 100+ per hit.<br><br>Mostly you can sum it up in one phrase:<br>If your getting hit, then you are already in trouble and a few points of Agi or Sta won't help.<br><br>Thayn<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Erudite Mage<br>Master Smith<br>Journeyman Tailor</td></tr>
